From e5ffe1816494896a7fcba75e340651fc6c00753d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 19:48:44 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fact-check with web search and cited source URLs

Claude's server-side web_search tool (web_search_20260209, GA on opus-4-8) is now
enabled for health/political/finance fact-checks, so verification is grounded in real
sources instead of training memory. _factcheck_with_web_search() runs the request,
follows pause_turn continuations through the server-side tool loop, and harvests the
URLs of every search result so they back-fill the sources list even if Claude omits
them from its JSON. Falls back to a no-search call if web search errors.

Refined fact-check rules per topic:
- Finance: skip predictions/opinions and moment-in-time spot prices; verify quantitative
  claims over a time span (multi-year growth, historical highs, dividend history) and
  legal/regulatory/reported-figure claims against filings and records.
- Health: verify against studies/guidelines and cite them.
- Political: verify demonstrably true/false factual claims against the record.
All topics: cite source URLs.

Travel location check now explicitly focuses on scanning comments for callouts that the
post isn't of the place it claims ("this is actually Bali not Maldives"), with confidence
keyed to how many commenters agree.

Note rendering: source URLs render as clickable [domain](url) links; claim entries accept
either a plain string or {claim, source} object. Sources/web_search controls added to
config.yaml (web_search, max_searches, max_tokens under fact_checking).

